From: Cole Leavitt <cole@unwrap.rs>
Subject: encoding_rs: import Select trait for portable_simd on rustc >= 1.95

Starting with rustc 1.95-nightly, Mask::select was moved from an inherent
method to the Select trait (core::simd::Select). Upstream encoding_rs 0.8.35
handles this via #[rustversion::since(1.95)], but Firefox's vendored copy
strips the rustversion dependency from the simd-accel feature, so the
conditional import is absent. Add the unconditional import — it's required
for any nightly >= 1.95 and the simd-accel feature is only used on nightly.

--- a/third_party/rust/encoding_rs/src/x_user_defined.rs
+++ b/third_party/rust/encoding_rs/src/x_user_defined.rs
@@ -15,6 +15,7 @@
     if #[cfg(feature = "simd-accel")] {
         use simd_funcs::*;
         use core::simd::u16x8;
+        use core::simd::Select;
         use core::simd::cmp::SimdPartialOrd;
 
         #[inline(always)]
